{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSThemesOrange\/documentation\/OUDSThemesOrange"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudsthemesorange\/orangethemeinputtagcomponenttokensprovider"]}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OrangeThemeInputTagComponentTokensProvider","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ Define your own provider for tag input component tokens","    \/\/ by inheriting from existing provider","    class CustomInputTagComponentTokensProvider: OrangeThemeInputTagComponentTokensProvider {","","        \/\/ Then override the tag component tokens you want.","","        override var borderRadius: BorderRadiusSemanticToken  { borders.radiusNone }","","        override var colorBgPressed: MultipleColorSemanticTokens { colors.actionPressed }","","        \/\/ ...","    }","","    \/\/ Or define your own provider from scratch","    class CustomInputTagComponentTokensProvider: InputTagComponentTokens {","","        \/\/ And implement maybe hundreds of tokens.","        \/\/ You are allowed to use semantic tokens providers if you want to define values.","    }"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Then, you can give this "},{"code":"CustomInputTagComponentTokensProvider","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to your own theme implementation:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["class LocalTheme: OrangeTheme {","","    override init() {","        super.init(inputTag: CustomInputTagComponentTokensProvider())","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"or to an already existing theme for example:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    OrangeT